				xmlns:cito="https://sparontologies.github.io/cito/current/cito.html#"
				xmlns:org="http://www.w3.org/ns/org#"/></xenoData>
	</teiHeader>
	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb n="2" facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary01_0.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date>Saturday 23</date></dateline>
				<p xml:id="a1">This morning when we got up it was <name type="weather">rainin<name
							type="weather"/>g and the <placeName>camp</placeName> was <name
							type="weather">wet and dreary</name>.</name> I felt as if I was glad
						it<name type="Weather"> rained</name> to get relieved. But it cleared off
					about <time>ten o'clock</time>. There was regimental drill but as our
						<objectName type="weapon">muskets </objectName>were freshly marked, I got
					excused, but we were out for dress parade &amp; had a march in review. We had
					the pleasure of welcoming <persName key="Seth Housel"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper071"
						>Seth Housel </persName>back this afternoon, and this evening <persName
						key="Jacob G. Beaver"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper003"
						>Beaver </persName>returned, bringing all that we expected of him, <persName
						key="George Shorkley"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper002"
						>George Shorkley</persName> is lieutenant of the guard today. We had an
						<objectName type="food">oyster pie</objectName> for dinner, but we were
					hurried &amp; didn't enjoy it.<objectName/></p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
</TEI>
